      </Figure>

      <h2>The Logos Deep-Dive</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Adversarial Systems Thinking</strong> — The system doesn't just scrape; it models the "enemy" (the anti-bot firewall) and adapts its fingerprint in real-time.</li>
        <li><strong>Schema Normalization</strong> — Mapping 50 inconsistent dialects of UCC data into a single, queryable relational model.</li>
        <li><strong>Observability as a Feature</strong> — In a 50-state system, you don't "fix bugs"; you manage "portal drift." I specified a logging architecture that treats every extraction as an auditable event.</li>
      </ul>

